[InvStG § 19](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/invstg_2018/__19.html) imposes a deemed-distribution levy (Vorabpauschale) on accumulating investment funds so they cannot grow tax-free indefinitely. [InvStG § 18](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/invstg_2018/__18.html) fixes the base: **Basisertrag = NAV_start × 0.7 × Basiszinssatz × months_held / 12**. Actual distributions are netted out per § 18 Abs. 1 Satz 3, [InvStG § 16 Abs. 1 Nr. 2](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/invstg_2018/__16.html) caps the result at the year's NAV gain (NAV_end − NAV_start), and [InvStG § 20](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/invstg_2018/__20.html) then applies the same Teilfreistellung rate that already routes actual distributions.

The 2025 Basiszinssatz is **2.53 %** (BMF-Schreiben dated 16 January 2025, IV C 1 - S 1980-1/19/10005:008). The Vorabpauschale is **laufender Ertrag** under § 32d Abs. 1 EStG (25% Abgeltungsteuer) and feeds § 20 Abs. 6 EStG netting as a non-stock-gain bucket (§ 20 Abs. 6 Satz 4 EStG forbids offsetting against stock losses).

